In this press briefing, Press Secretary Robert Gibbs and National Incident Commander Thad Allen provide an update on the BP oil spill and the response efforts. Allen mentions that a third production vessel, the Helix Producer, will be brought online next week, which will increase the capacity to 53,000 barrels per day. He also provides updates on the relief wells and the onshore and near-shore skimming and recovery operations. Gibbs discusses the upcoming climate bill and the administration's position on putting a price on carbon. He also addresses concerns about a double-dip recession and the need for continued economic recovery efforts. Other topics discussed include the new 20-meter safety zone, the offshore drilling moratorium, unemployment insurance, and the possibility of immigration reform.